review_blob: Bottleat home. Spicy, cinnamon, nutmeg. Pleasurable pumpkin taste but not overpoweringly so. A nice slight cream/vanilla finish almost like a dollop of whipped cream on top of pumpkin pre.
Bottle, light hoppy smell. Slightly sweet with grapefruit notes and a subtle ipa finish. Pairs very well with something sweet, spicy and chocolaty.

Bottle into a goblet glass at home. Rich Dark sepia color with an almost rust colored head. Subtle flavors all over. I was expecting more of a spiced pumpkin taste and it was more like drinking a heavier New Castle with a hint of spices.
Had on draft in Ernie?s bar and pizza. One of the nicer fruit beers I?ve had. Not sweet like a cider but still very flavorful. Light and crisp..
Bottle. Light, refreshing taste. Paired very well with Bison ribs and Guy?s chicken taco from Tocabe?s in Denver, Co.
